<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="96" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/605</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Belgian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Van Straten</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 2674</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-28">June 28, 1935</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: By your letter
                                dated the twenty-seventh of this month,<note n="32" xml:id="d96fn32">Letter missing from Department files.</note> Your Excellency
                                was kind enough to send me a new <pb facs="0200" n="124" xml:id="pg_124"/> draft for the general provisions which are to
                                complete the Commercial Agreement recently concluded between our two
                                countries.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor of advising Your Excellency that I have forwarded
                                this proposal to the King’s Government. As soon as the latter
                                advises me of its point of view on this subject, I shall hasten to
                                inform Your Excellency thereof, and I hope, as you do, that the last
                                phase of our commercial negotiations will be terminated very
                                shortly.</p>
                            <p>I take [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cte</hi>. R. <hi rend="smallcaps">v. Straten</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>